Best practices
==============

Core principles
--------------

#. **Version control everything**: Keep all pipeline configuration in your CDK package
#. **Test changes in development**: Deploy to a development pipeline before production
#. **Use gradual rollout**: Test PipelineUpdate Target on non-critical pipelines first
#. **Monitor deployments**: Watch the PipelineUpdate stage for any issues during rollout
#. **Document changes**: Include clear commit messages for pipeline modifications
#. **Review permissions**: Regularly audit Bindle permissions for your pipelines

Version control strategies
--------------------------

**Branch-based pipeline management**:

.. code-block:: typescript

   // Configure different pipelines for different branches
   const branchConfig = {
     'mainline': {
       pipelineName: 'my-service-prod',
       approvalRequired: true,
       deployToProduction: true
     },
     'development': {
       pipelineName: 'my-service-dev',
       approvalRequired: false,
       deployToProduction: false
     },
     'release/*': {
       pipelineName: 'my-service-staging',
       approvalRequired: true,
       deployToProduction: false
     }
   };

   const currentBranch = process.env.BRANCH_NAME || 'mainline';
   const config = branchConfig[currentBranch] || branchConfig['development'];

   const pipeline = new DeploymentPipeline(this, 'Pipeline', {
     ...config,
     createLegacyPipelineStage: false
   });

**Pipeline configuration as code patterns**:

.. code-block:: typescript

   // Externalize configuration for reusability
   import { PipelineConfig } from './config/pipeline-config';

   export class PipelineFactory {
     static createPipeline(scope: Construct, environment: string): DeploymentPipeline {
       const config = PipelineConfig.load(environment);

       return new DeploymentPipeline(scope, `Pipeline-${environment}`, {
         createLegacyPipelineStage: false,
         ...config,

         // Environment-specific overrides
         approvalWorkflows: environment === 'production' 
           ? config.approvalWorkflows 
           : [],

         // Conditional features
         enableMetrics: environment !== 'development',
         enableTracing: environment !== 'development',

         // Security policies
         securityScanningPolicy: {
           enabled: true,
           blockOnHighSeverity: environment === 'production',
           scanTypes: ['SAST', 'DAST', 'Dependencies']
         }
       });
     }
   }

Monitoring and observability
----------------------------

**CloudWatch integration**:

.. code-block:: typescript

   // Add CloudWatch alarms for pipeline health
   import { Alarm, Metric, TreatMissingData } from '@aws-cdk/aws-cloudwatch';

   const pipelineUpdateFailures = new Metric({
     namespace: 'AWS/Pipelines',
     metricName: 'PipelineUpdateFailures',
     dimensions: {
       PipelineName: pipeline.pipelineName
     }
   });

   new Alarm(this, 'PipelineUpdateFailureAlarm', {
     metric: pipelineUpdateFailures,
     threshold: 1,
     evaluationPeriods: 1,
     treatMissingData: TreatMissingData.NOT_BREACHING,
     alarmDescription: 'Pipeline update failed - investigate immediately'
   });

