**Separation of duties**:

.. code-block:: typescript

   // Separate pipeline management from deployment
   const pipelineManagementRole = new Role(this, 'PipelineManagementRole', {
     assumedBy: new ServicePrincipal('pipelines.amazonaws.com'),
     description: 'Role for pipeline structure updates only'
   });

   const deploymentRole = new Role(this, 'DeploymentRole', {
     assumedBy: new ServicePrincipal('codedeploy.amazonaws.com'),
     description: 'Role for application deployments only'
   });

   // Ensure roles cannot assume each other
   pipelineManagementRole.addToPolicy(new PolicyStatement({
     effect: Effect.DENY,
     actions: ['sts:AssumeRole'],
     resources: [deploymentRole.roleArn]
   }));

When to use
===========

**Recommended scenarios**:

* New pipelines being created with CDK
* Existing pipelines ready for modernization  
* Teams wanting better GitOps workflows
* Multi-region or multi-account deployments
* Pipelines requiring frequent configuration updates
* Complex pipelines with multiple deployment groups
* Pipelines requiring strict audit and compliance

**Specific use cases**:

#. **Microservices architectures**:

   .. code-block:: typescript

      // Manage multiple service pipelines from single CDK
      const services = ['auth', 'payment', 'inventory', 'shipping'];

      services.forEach(service => {
        new DeploymentPipeline(this, `${service}-pipeline`, {
          pipelineName: `microservice-${service}`,
          createLegacyPipelineStage: false,
          // Shared configuration
          ...sharedConfig,
          // Service-specific overrides
          ...serviceConfigs[service]
        });
      });

#. **Multi-tenant SaaS platforms**:

   .. code-block:: typescript

      // Per-tenant pipeline configuration
      interface TenantConfig {
        name: string;
        tier: 'basic' | 'premium' | 'enterprise';
        regions: string[];
        customDomains?: string[];
