Implement gradual rollout strategies
------------------------------------

When adopting PipelineUpdate Target:

#. Start with non-critical pipelines to gain experience
#. Create a rollback plan before migrating production pipelines
#. Monitor the first few deployments closely
#. Document any issues and resolutions for your team
#. Gradually expand to more critical pipelines

**Phased rollout plan**:

.. code-block:: typescript

   // Phase 1: Development pipelines (Week 1-2)
   export class Phase1Rollout {
     readonly pipelines = [
       'service-dev-pipeline',
       'experimental-features-pipeline'
     ];

     readonly validationCriteria = {
       successRate: 0.95,  // 95% success rate
       deploymentTime: 300, // Max 5 minutes
       rollbackTime: 60    // Rollback under 1 minute
     };
   }

   // Phase 2: Staging pipelines (Week 3-4)
   export class Phase2Rollout {
     readonly pipelines = [
       'service-staging-pipeline',
       'integration-test-pipeline'
     ];

     readonly validationCriteria = {
       successRate: 0.98,
       deploymentTime: 240,
       rollbackTime: 30
     };
   }

   // Phase 3: Production pipelines (Week 5-6)
   export class Phase3Rollout {
     readonly pipelines = [
       'service-prod-pipeline',
       'customer-facing-api-pipeline'
     ];

     readonly validationCriteria = {
       successRate: 0.995,
       deploymentTime: 180,
       rollbackTime: 15,
       requiresApproval: true,
       requiresMCM: true
     };
   }

**Monitoring during rollout**:

.. code-block:: bash

   #!/bin/bash
   # Monitor pipeline updates during rollout

   PIPELINE=$1
   START_TIME=$(date +%s)

   # Watch for PipelineUpdate stage completion
   while true; do
     STATUS=$(aws pipelines describe-pipeline \
       --name $PIPELINE \
       --query 'pipeline.stages[?name==`PipelineUpdate`].status' \
       --output text)

     case $STATUS in
       "SUCCEEDED")
         END_TIME=$(date +%s)
         DURATION=$((END_TIME - START_TIME))
         echo " Pipeline update completed in ${DURATION}s"

         # Log metrics
         aws cloudwatch put-metric-data \
           --namespace "PipelineRollout" \
           --metric-name "UpdateDuration" \
           --value $DURATION \
           --dimensions Pipeline=$PIPELINE
         break
         ;;
       "FAILED")
         echo " Pipeline update failed - initiating rollback"
         pipeline configmode --offboard --pipelineName=$PIPELINE
         exit 1
         ;;
       "IN_PROGRESS")
         echo " Update in progress..."
         sleep 10
         ;;
     esac
   done

